fields.descriptive_line: Set of eighty-six quilting templates, Durham, 1900-1932
fields.physical_description: Set of eighty-six quilting templates. A collection of paper and card templates used in the quilting of bedcovers. Made mostly from brown paper with some examples cut from pink coloured card, the templates show a wide range of quilting patterns. These include stylised flowers and leaf designs, scalloping, worm chain, feathering, hammock, shells and other patterns. Various sizes.
